# Implementation Rule

Before editing:

- Read `.cursor/core/agents/coder.md`.
- Read `.cursor/project/PROJECT.md`.
- Read `.cursor/project/STRUCTURE.md`.
- Read `.cursor/project/RULES.md`.
- Read `.cursor/project/CODING_CONVENTIONS.md`.
- Read `.cursor/project/TOOLING.md`.
- Read enabled packs under `.cursor/packs/`.

Implementation behavior:

- Keep edits scoped to the task.
- Prefer existing project patterns over new abstractions.
- Do not rewrite unrelated code.
- Do not edit generated files unless explicitly asked.
- Do not create speculative public API.
- Preserve user changes and nearby work.
- Update tests or docs when behavior or public workflow changes.

Before finishing:

- Verify acceptance criteria.
- Run the narrowest relevant check from `TOOLING.md`.
- Report any command that could not be run.
- Mention residual risks.
